---
description: Clean Architecture enforcement and Dependency Rule
applyTo: "backend/**/*.py"
---



Strict dependency direction — always inward, never outward.


```
backend/src/{{ project_slug }}/
├── core/                     # Domain layer (INNERMOST) — ZERO external deps
│   ├── constants.py          # Named constants (UPPER_SNAKE_CASE, no Final)
│   ├── types.py              # Shared type aliases
│   ├── validators.py         # Pure domain validators
│   ├── entities/             # Domain entities (inherit Entity, dataclass(slots=True))
│   │   └── base.py           # Entity base class
│   ├── value_objects/        # Immutable VOs (frozen=True, slots=True)
│   ├── events/               # Domain events (frozen=True, slots=True)
│   ├── enums/                # Domain enums (StrEnum + @unique + auto())
│   ├── exceptions/           # DomainError hierarchy (NotFound, Conflict, Validation, Authorization)
│   ├── interfaces/           # Protocols: Repository[T], CacheGateway, EventBus, UnitOfWork, etc.
│   └── specifications/       # Domain specification objects
│
├── application/              # Use cases, orchestration, DTOs
│   ├── services/             # Inherit BaseService (services/base.py), depend on port protocols ONLY
│   ├── commands/             # Write-side inputs (frozen dataclasses)
│   ├── queries/              # Read-side inputs (frozen dataclasses)
│   ├── dtos/                 # Inherit BaseDTO (dtos/base.py), Annotated[..., Field(...)]
│   ├── mappers/              # Entity ↔ DTO mapping functions
│   └── tasks/                # Async task definitions (Celery signatures)
│
├── infrastructure/           # Concrete gateway/repository implementations
│   ├── persistence/          # DB: ORM models, repos, UoW, session
│   │   ├── orm/              # SQLAlchemy 2.0+ (Mapped[] + mapped_column())
│   │   ├── repositories/     # Concrete repo implementations (base.py + per-entity)
│   │   ├── unit_of_work/     # SQLAlchemy UoW
│   │   └── session.py        # Async engine + session factory (single definition)
│   ├── cache/                # Redis + in-memory (implement CacheGateway)
│   ├── messaging/            # Event bus (implement EventBus)
│   ├── auth/                 # JWT / auth infrastructure
│   ├── email/                # SMTP + console email infrastructure
│   ├── storage/              # Local + Azure Blob storage infrastructure
│   └── external/             # httpx clients, third-party API infrastructure
│
├── presentation/             # Presentation layer (OUTERMOST)
│   ├── api/                  # FastAPI REST
│   │   ├── app.py            # create_api_app() -> FastAPI
│   │   ├── dependencies.py   # ALL Depends() — DI wiring
│   │   ├── middleware/       # Rate limiting, request ID, CORS, error handling
│   │   ├── routes/           # Thin routes — ZERO business logic
│   │   └── schemas/          # Request/response Pydantic schemas
│   ├── graphql/              # Strawberry GraphQL (conditional)
│   ├── web/                  # Jinja2 web UI
│   │   └── controllers/      # Call application services, never infrastructure
│   └── cli/                  # Click CLI
│       └── app.py            # cli() -> click.Group
│
├── composition/              # Dependency injection wiring
│   └── container.py          # DI composition root — wires protocols → adapters
│
├── config/                   # Settings, logging{% if use_celery %}, Celery{% endif %}

│   ├── settings/             # Environment-specific settings (base, dev, prod, etc.)
│   └── logging.py            # Structured logging configuration
│
├── ai/                       # AI integration vertical (CONDITIONAL — only if use_ai)
│   ├── prompts/              # Prompt templates and chains
│   ├── agents/               # AI agent definitions
│   └── tools/                # AI tool integrations
│
└── utils/                    # Framework-agnostic, pure functions, stdlib ONLY
    ├── logger_factory.py     # Structured logging setup
    └── ...                   # crypto, file, json, string, timing, retry, pagination
```


```
core/ ← application/ ← infrastructure/
                      ← presentation/
                      ← config/
utils/ ← (all layers may import; utils imports from NO project layer)
```

| Layer                              | May Import From                                              | NEVER Imports From                     |
| ---------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------ | -------------------------------------- |
| **Core (core/)**                   | stdlib, utils/                                               | application/, infrastructure/, presentation/, config/, ai/ |
| **Application (application/)**     | core/ (protocols + base classes), ai/ (services, models — vertical), utils/ | infrastructure/, presentation/, config/             |
| **Infrastructure (infrastructure/)**     | core/ (protocols), application/ (DTOs, mappers), utils/, libs | presentation/, ai/                            |
| **Presentation (presentation/)**          | application/ (services, DTOs), core/ (exceptions, enums, constants, interfaces), config/, utils/, ai/ (models, services — vertical per ADR) | infrastructure/ (use DI)                     |
| **config/**                        | core/enums/ (Environment), utils/, external libs             | application/, infrastructure/, presentation/, ai/   |
| **ai/**                            | core/, application/, utils/, external AI libs (langchain, openai) | presentation/, config/, infrastructure/             |
| **utils/**                         | stdlib ONLY                                                  | ALL other project layers               |

**Note on ai/ vertical module:** Per decision D002, `ai/` is a separate top-level vertical module, not a Clean Architecture layer. Standard inner/outer layer restrictions don't apply to it. Both `application/` and `presentation/` may import ai/ models and services. The ai/ module itself must not import from `presentation/`, `config/`, or `infrastructure/`.

**Known exception:** `presentation/graphql/permissions.py.jinja` directly imports `JWTAdapter` from `infrastructure/` (Presentation importing from Infrastructure) due to missing auth interface and DI wiring infrastructure. This is a documented FIXME pending proper auth DI implementation.


| Concern                                  | ONLY In                 |
| ---------------------------------------- | ----------------------- |
| HTTP status codes, request/response      | `presentation/api/`            |
| CLI exit codes, terminal output          | `presentation/cli/`            |
| HTML rendering, form handling            | `presentation/web/`            |
| Business rules, domain invariants        | `core/`                 |
| Use case orchestration, DTO mapping      | `application/`          |
| Database queries, ORM, SQL, sessions     | `infrastructure/persistence/` |
| Cache get/set/delete                     | `infrastructure/cache/`       |
| Event publish/subscribe                  | `infrastructure/messaging/`   |
| Environment variables, settings          | `config/settings.py`    |
| Pure, framework-agnostic helpers         | `utils/`                |


```python
from {{ project_slug }}.core.entities.user import User
from {{ project_slug }}.core.interfaces.cache import CacheGateway
from {{ project_slug }}.application.services.user_service import UserService

from {{ project_slug }}.infrastructure.persistence import UserRepository  # core → infrastructure
from {{ project_slug }}.presentation.api.routes import router              # core → presentation
```


ALL entry points use factory functions — no global mutable state:

- `create_api_app() -> FastAPI` in `presentation/api/app.py`
- `create_web_app() -> FastAPI` in `presentation/web/app.py`
- `cli() -> click.Group` in `presentation/cli/app.py`
{%- if use_celery %}
- `create_celery_app() -> Celery` in `config/celery.py`
{%- endif %}


- `composition/container.py` wires gateway/repository protocols to concrete implementations
- Constructor injection via typed parameters
- No service locator pattern, no global mutable state
- Routes NEVER instantiate dependencies — use `presentation/api/dependencies.py`
